<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><sqlb_project><db path="dataEl.db" readonly="0" foreign_keys="1" case_sensitive_like="0" temp_store="0" wal_autocheckpoint="1000" synchronous="2"/><attached/><window><main_tabs open="structure browser pragmas query" current="0"/></window><tab_structure><column_width id="0" width="300"/><column_width id="1" width="0"/><column_width id="2" width="100"/><column_width id="3" width="1659"/><column_width id="4" width="0"/><expanded_item id="0" parent="1"/><expanded_item id="1" parent="0"/><expanded_item id="2" parent="0"/><expanded_item id="1" parent="1"/><expanded_item id="2" parent="1"/><expanded_item id="3" parent="1"/></tab_structure><tab_browse><table title="story" custom_title="0" dock_id="1" table="4,5:mainstory"/><dock_state state="000000ff00000000fd00000001000000020000045e000002b6fc0100000001fb000000160064006f0063006b00420072006f007700730065003101000000000000045e0000013600ffffff000002580000000000000004000000040000000800000008fc00000000"/><default_encoding codec=""/><browse_table_settings><table schema="main" name="sqlite_sequence" show_row_id="0" encoding="" plot_x_axis="" unlock_view_pk="_rowid_" freeze_columns="0"><sort/><column_widths><column index="1" value="39"/><column index="2" value="29"/></column_widths><filter_values/><conditional_formats/><row_id_formats/><display_formats/><hidden_columns/><plot_y_axes/><global_filter/></table><table schema="main" name="story" show_row_id="0" encoding="" plot_x_axis="" unlock_view_pk="_rowid_" freeze_columns="0"><sort/><column_widths><column index="1" value="29"/><column index="2" value="55"/><column index="3" value="300"/><column index="4" value="300"/><column index="5" value="117"/><column index="6" value="124"/><column index="7" value="124"/><column index="8" value="124"/><column index="9" value="124"/><column index="10" value="300"/></column_widths><filter_values/><conditional_formats/><row_id_formats/><display_formats/><hidden_columns/><plot_y_axes/><global_filter/></table><table schema="main" name="topic" show_row_id="0" encoding="" plot_x_axis="" unlock_view_pk="_rowid_" freeze_columns="0"><sort/><column_widths><column index="1" value="29"/><column index="2" value="35"/><column index="3" value="300"/></column_widths><filter_values/><conditional_formats/><row_id_formats/><display_formats/><hidden_columns/><plot_y_axes/><global_filter/></table></browse_table_settings></tab_browse><tab_sql><sql name="SQL 1">-- 31. Family &amp; Relationships (B2) - topic_id = 31
INSERT INTO &quot;story&quot; (&quot;topic_id&quot;, &quot;story_content&quot;, &quot;question&quot;, &quot;option_a&quot;, &quot;option_b&quot;, &quot;option_c&quot;, &quot;option_d&quot;, &quot;correct_answer&quot;, &quot;explanation_vi&quot;) VALUES 
(31, 'Intergenerational conflict often stems from differing values shaped by contrasting historical contexts. While the younger generation prioritizes personal autonomy and self-expression, older members may emphasize stability and traditional social cohesion. Bridging this gap requires both sides to practice active listening rather than simply waiting for their turn to speak. If mutual respect is maintained, these differences can become a source of strength rather than friction. Ultimately, fostering open communication is the cornerstone of a resilient family unit that can withstand external societal pressures.', 'What is the root of intergenerational conflict?', 'Lack of money', 'Differing values/contexts', 'Technological barriers', 'Physical distance', 'Differing values/contexts', 'Xung đột thế hệ bắt nguồn từ các giá trị khác biệt.'),
(31, 'Healthy romantic relationships are characterized by interdependence rather than total reliance on one another. Each partner should maintain their own identity and professional pursuits while nurturing their shared bond. Conflict is inevitable in any committed relationship, but the key lies in how the couple navigates these disagreements. Couples who practice constructive criticism often find that their bond deepens after resolving tough issues together. It is this resilience that separates fleeting romances from long-lasting partnerships.', 'What characterizes a healthy relationship?', 'Total reliance', 'Interdependence', 'No conflict', 'Complete autonomy', 'Interdependence', 'Mối quan hệ lành mạnh dựa trên sự phụ thuộc lẫn nhau.'),
(31, 'The concept of &quot;chosen family&quot; has gained significant prominence, especially among those who feel alienated from their biological roots. For many, these bonds are forged through shared experiences, deep empathy, and unconditional support. Such relationships prove that blood ties are not the only measure of genuine connection. While biological families are traditional, chosen families provide a sense of belonging for individuals who seek acceptance. This evolution in family structures reflects a broader shift towards valuing emotional resonance over social convention.', 'What does the text suggest about family?', 'Blood is everything', 'Chosen families are invalid', 'Connections go beyond biology', 'Social conventions are rigid', 'Connections go beyond biology', 'Tình cảm gia đình không chỉ giới hạn ở huyết thống.'),
(31, 'Parenting in the digital age presents a unique set of challenges regarding privacy and screen time exposure. Parents must navigate the thin line between monitoring their children for safety and respecting their need for digital independence. Establishing clear boundaries early on is essential to prevent behavioral issues later in adolescence. When parents lead by example, children are more likely to adopt healthier habits themselves. Maintaining a balance between digital connectivity and real-world interaction is critical for a child’s holistic development.', 'What is a challenge for modern parenting?', 'Financial stability', 'Balancing privacy and safety', 'Cooking meals', 'Choosing schools', 'Balancing privacy and safety', 'Thách thức là cân bằng quyền riêng tư và an toàn.'),
(31, 'Empathy is the invisible glue that holds complex family dynamics together over many years. When family members are willing to step into each other’s shoes, misunderstanding becomes an opportunity for growth. It requires vulnerability to admit mistakes and patience to see things from a different perspective. Families that cultivate this trait can navigate even the most tumultuous crises without breaking apart. Ultimately, empathy transforms a group of related individuals into a true team.', 'What is the &quot;invisible glue&quot; of family?', 'Money', 'Empathy', 'Strict rules', 'Technology', 'Empathy', 'Sự thấu cảm giúp gắn kết gia đình.'),
(31, 'The transition from being a child to being a caregiver for one’s aging parents is a profound life shift. It demands a reversal of traditional roles that can be emotionally taxing for both parties involved. Navigating medical decisions and daily care requires immense sensitivity and clear communication with siblings. Despite the difficulty, this period offers a final chance to honor the sacrifices made by the previous generation. It is a time that tests the strength of family bonds and reinforces the importance of mutual care.', 'What makes the caregiver transition difficult?', 'Financial loss', 'Role reversal and emotions', 'Lack of time', 'Distance', 'Role reversal and emotions', 'Sự đảo ngược vai trò là một thách thức cảm xúc.'),
(31, 'Extended family networks, though sometimes less prominent in urban settings, remain vital for long-term social support. They offer a safety net that smaller nuclear families cannot provide during times of economic or personal crisis. Maintaining these connections requires intentional effort, especially when families are geographically dispersed. Despite the time commitment, the sense of heritage and continuity provided by aunts, uncles, and cousins is irreplaceable. They provide a broader sense of self and an expanded worldview for children.', 'What is a benefit of extended family?', 'Always close by', 'A safety net of support', 'No conflict', 'Free childcare', 'A safety net of support', 'Đại gia đình cung cấp mạng lưới hỗ trợ an toàn.');

-- 32. Daily Routine (B2) - topic_id = 32
INSERT INTO &quot;story&quot; (&quot;topic_id&quot;, &quot;story_content&quot;, &quot;question&quot;, &quot;option_a&quot;, &quot;option_b&quot;, &quot;option_c&quot;, &quot;option_d&quot;, &quot;correct_answer&quot;, &quot;explanation_vi&quot;) VALUES 
(32, 'Optimizing one’s daily routine is less about squeezing in more tasks and more about prioritizing high-impact activities. By front-loading the most demanding cognitive tasks to the early morning hours, one can capitalize on peak mental clarity. Following this, the afternoon is reserved for routine administrative duties and collaborative meetings. This structured approach prevents the common pitfall of decision fatigue as the day progresses. When implemented consistently, this rhythm significantly boosts long-term productivity and overall well-being.', 'Why should demanding tasks be done in the morning?', 'To save time', 'Peak mental clarity', 'They are easier', 'To avoid meetings', 'Peak mental clarity', 'Buổi sáng là lúc tinh thần minh mẫn nhất.'),
(32, 'The practice of &quot;deep work&quot;—periods of distraction-free concentration—has become a cornerstone of my professional routine. By silencing notifications and isolating specific time blocks for complex projects, I can achieve in three hours what used to take an entire day. It requires significant self-discipline, especially in an era of constant digital bombardment. Once mastered, however, it provides a sense of accomplishment that mere busywork cannot provide. This strategy not only improves output quality but also protects the brain from the fragmentation caused by multitasking.', 'What is the main benefit of &quot;deep work&quot;?', 'Higher quality/faster output', 'Social status', 'Saving money', 'Reduced salary', 'Higher quality/faster output', 'Deep work nâng cao chất lượng công việc.'),
(32, 'Routine maintenance of one’s physical health is arguably the most neglected part of a busy professional’s schedule. Incorporating movement, such as light stretching or brisk walking, into the daily rhythm is not a luxury but a necessity for long-term health. Many professionals wait until they are symptomatic to take action, which is a fundamentally flawed approach. By treating exercise as a non-negotiable appointment, one ensures that the body remains capable of supporting the mind’s ambitions. Consistency, rather than intensity, is the true secret to longevity.', 'What is the common mistake professionals make?', 'Exercise too much', 'Wait until they are sick', 'Work too hard', 'Sleep too little', 'Wait until they are sick', 'Sai lầm là đợi đến khi bị bệnh mới hành động.'),
(32, 'Reflective journaling before ending the workday has become an essential habit for professional growth. It allows me to decompress, analyze the day’s wins, and identify areas that require adjustment for tomorrow. This brief period of intentional thought prevents work-related stress from leaking into my personal life. It also ensures that I do not repeat the same strategic errors, thereby fostering continuous improvement. Over time, these small reflections compile into a comprehensive map of my professional evolution.', 'What is the benefit of daily reflection?', 'To sleep faster', 'Continuous improvement', 'To make money', 'To impress the boss', 'Continuous improvement', 'Nhật ký phản tư giúp cải thiện không ngừng.'),
(32, 'Establishing a &quot;shutdown ritual&quot; at the end of the day signals to the brain that the workday is officially over. This may involve closing all browser tabs, tidying the desk, and reviewing the to-do list for the next day. Such rituals are crucial for breaking the cycle of constant connectivity that defines modern work. They allow the mind to shift gears and dedicate quality attention to family and hobbies. Without this boundary, work tends to expand into every available moment, leading to inevitable exhaustion.', 'What is a &quot;shutdown ritual&quot;?', 'Turning off the computer', 'Closing apps and reviewing to-do list', 'Going to bed', 'Eating dinner', 'Closing apps and reviewing to-do list', 'Nghi thức kết thúc công việc giúp tách biệt cuộc sống.'),
(32, 'Early morning exposure to natural light is scientifically proven to regulate our circadian rhythm more effectively than any artificial stimulant. Even ten minutes of sunlight can boost alertness and regulate hormonal production, making the rest of the day more stable. Many people inadvertently sabotage their own biological clocks by staying in dark environments until midday. Prioritizing light exposure is a simple, high-leverage change that enhances both mood and focus. It is the cheapest and most effective tool for managing daily energy levels.', 'What is the benefit of morning sunlight?', 'It saves money', 'Regulates circadian rhythm', 'It replaces exercise', 'It cures all illnesses', 'Regulates circadian rhythm', 'Ánh sáng sớm giúp điều hòa nhịp sinh học.'),
(32, 'Preparing the night before is the ultimate secret to a frictionless morning routine. By laying out clothes and finalizing the breakfast menu, one reduces the number of small decisions that drain mental energy upon waking. This conservation of willpower allows for a calm and focused start to the day. It turns the morning from a chaotic race against the clock into a planned sequence of deliberate actions. A well-planned night is essentially an investment in a productive morning.', 'How does preparing at night help?', 'It makes you sleep longer', 'Reduces morning decision fatigue', 'It saves money', 'It is fun', 'Reduces morning decision fatigue', 'Chuẩn bị từ tối hôm trước giúp giảm mệt mỏi vào sáng sớm.');

-- 33. Food &amp; Cooking (B2) - topic_id = 33
INSERT INTO &quot;story&quot; (&quot;topic_id&quot;, &quot;story_content&quot;, &quot;question&quot;, &quot;option_a&quot;, &quot;option_b&quot;, &quot;option_c&quot;, &quot;option_d&quot;, &quot;correct_answer&quot;, &quot;explanation_vi&quot;) VALUES 
(33, 'The culinary industry is experiencing a profound shift toward hyper-local sourcing and seasonal ingredients. Chefs are moving away from globalized supply chains to reduce their carbon footprint and highlight regional flavors. This approach requires more flexibility, as menus must change based on what is available in the local market each week. While it presents logistical challenges, the quality and freshness of the final dish are unparalleled. Consumers are increasingly willing to pay a premium for this commitment to sustainability and provenance.', 'What is the main driver behind the shift to local sourcing?', 'Higher profits', 'Environmental concerns', 'Easier logistics', 'Global demand', 'Environmental concerns', 'Xu hướng ẩm thực hướng tới bền vững và giảm dấu chân carbon.'),
(33, 'Sous-vide cooking, once reserved for professional laboratory-like kitchens, has become accessible to home cooks due to technological democratization. By maintaining a precise, constant water temperature, this method guarantees consistent results that conventional stovetop cooking often misses. Proteins become tender, and vegetables retain their vibrant colors and nutritional density. Though it requires specialized equipment, the learning curve is surprisingly manageable. Ultimately, it elevates the home-cooking experience to near-professional standards.', 'What is the advantage of sous-vide?', 'It is fast', 'Consistent results', 'No equipment needed', 'It is cheap', 'Consistent results', 'Sous-vide giúp món ăn đạt độ hoàn hảo ổn định.'),
(33, 'Fermentation is both an ancient preservation technique and a sophisticated flavor-building tool. Microorganisms break down compounds, creating complex profiles that cannot be achieved through heat alone. From the sharp tang of sourdough to the umami bomb of aged miso, fermentation adds a layer of depth that enhances the entire palate. Beyond taste, these foods are probiotic powerhouses that support a healthy gut microbiome. Mastering these techniques requires patience and observation, but the results are transformative.', 'What does fermentation add to food?', 'Complex flavors', 'Too much sugar', 'Blandness', 'Heat only', 'Complex flavors', 'Lên men tạo ra tầng hương vị phức tạp.'),
(33, 'The art of food styling has become as important as the flavor itself in the age of social media. Chefs must now consider how a dish will appear on camera before they even begin the cooking process. While some argue that this prioritizes aesthetics over substance, others see it as a necessary evolution of modern gastronomy. Balancing visual appeal with genuine taste is the new challenge for young chefs. The dish must be a feast for the eyes and the palate simultaneously.', 'What is the challenge for modern chefs?', 'Cooking fast', 'Visual appeal vs. taste', 'Cheaper ingredients', 'Finding recipes', 'Visual appeal vs. taste', 'Thách thức là cân bằng hình thức và hương vị.'),
(33, 'The farm-to-table movement has forced a re-evaluation of our relationship with seasonality. Modern consumers often expect any ingredient year-round, which requires industrial intervention and long-distance transport. Returning to seasonal eating encourages an appreciation for the natural cycle of the Earth. It also forces home cooks to become more creative when certain products are unavailable. This connection to nature makes the act of cooking more meaningful and grounded.', 'What does seasonal eating encourage?', 'Industrial farming', 'Appreciation for natural cycles', 'Global shipping', 'Buying canned food', 'Appreciation for natural cycles', 'Ăn theo mùa giúp kết nối với tự nhiên.'),
(33, 'Understanding the science of flavor pairing can elevate home cooking to restaurant quality. By identifying molecular commonalities between ingredients, cooks can create harmonious combinations that defy tradition. For instance, pairing chocolate with blue cheese might seem strange, but their chemical overlap makes it a delicacy. This analytical approach encourages experimentation and breaks down the fear of failure in the kitchen. It is a fusion of science and creativity.', 'What helps create harmonious combinations?', 'Molecular commonalities', 'Random choice', 'Price', 'Speed', 'Molecular commonalities', 'Sự tương đồng phân tử giúp kết hợp thực phẩm.'),
(33, 'Food waste remains one of the largest silent issues in modern kitchens. Repurposing scraps—such as turning vegetable peels into stock or stale bread into puddings—is an essential culinary skill. It requires a mindset of resourcefulness that many modern cooks have lost. By minimizing waste, we not only save money but also acknowledge the effort that went into producing our ingredients. It is a simple but impactful step toward a more sustainable lifestyle.', 'What is a way to reduce food waste?', 'Throwing scraps', 'Repurposing scraps', 'Buying more', 'Ordering out', 'Repurposing scraps', 'Tái chế nguyên liệu thừa giúp giảm lãng phí.');

-- 34. Travel &amp; Tourism (B2) - topic_id = 34
INSERT INTO &quot;story&quot; (&quot;topic_id&quot;, &quot;story_content&quot;, &quot;question&quot;, &quot;option_a&quot;, &quot;option_b&quot;, &quot;option_c&quot;, &quot;option_d&quot;, &quot;correct_answer&quot;, &quot;explanation_vi&quot;) VALUES 
(34, 'Ecotourism is often marketed as a pristine solution, but it requires critical scrutiny to avoid &quot;greenwashing.&quot; True ecotourism should directly benefit local communities and fund conservation efforts rather than just providing a guilt-free travel experience. Travelers must demand transparency from operators to ensure their money is actually preserving the destination. When managed correctly, it provides an economic alternative to destructive industries like logging or poaching. Without oversight, however, it can still lead to the degradation of the very natural beauty tourists come to see.', 'What is the danger of ecotourism?', 'Too expensive', 'Greenwashing', 'No benefits', 'Limited travel', 'Greenwashing', 'Du lịch sinh thái cần cảnh giác với greenwashing.'),
(34, 'The rise of &quot;slow travel&quot; is a direct reaction to the frantic, checklist-based tourism of the past. By spending weeks in a single region rather than days, travelers can form genuine connections with the culture. This approach significantly reduces the environmental impact of constant transport and supports local small businesses. It transforms the trip from a series of photo opportunities into an immersive learning experience. For those with the privilege of time, it is the most respectful and rewarding way to explore the world.', 'What defines &quot;slow travel&quot;?', 'More flights', 'Immersive, long-term stays', 'Visiting many cities', 'Checklist tourism', 'Immersive, long-term stays', 'Du lịch chậm giúp trải nghiệm sâu sắc hơn.'),
(34, 'Overtourism has reached a breaking point in several iconic global cities, leading to restrictive regulations on visitor numbers. Authorities are now grappling with the balance between the economic benefits of tourism and the quality of life for residents. In places like Venice or Amsterdam, local life is being displaced by short-term rentals and souvenir shops. Solving this crisis will require a fundamental rethink of how we value travel as a commodity. Sustainable tourism must prioritize the inhabitant’s well-being above the tourist’s desire for convenience.', 'What is the main challenge of overtourism?', 'Too many hotels', 'Balance between profit and resident well-being', 'High fuel costs', 'Poor transport', 'Balance between profit and resident well-being', 'Thách thức là cân bằng lợi ích du lịch và đời sống dân cư.'),
(34, 'Culinary tourism has transformed how travelers choose their destinations. People now plan entire vacations around street food markets, regional specialties, or specific winemaking regions. This trend has put small towns on the global map, providing economic revitalization. However, it also brings the risk of gentrification to local markets. When street food becomes a tourist commodity, prices often rise, pushing out the local working class. It is a double-edged sword that requires careful management by local authorities.', 'What is a risk of culinary tourism?', 'No food', 'Gentrification/price rise', 'Too many tourists', 'Bad quality', 'Gentrification/price rise', 'Du lịch ẩm thực có thể gây lạm phát giá cả.'),
(34, 'Technological advancement in travel has made planning seamless, yet it has stripped away the &quot;serendipity of the unknown.&quot; We now have real-time reviews for every restaurant and precise maps for every route. While this minimizes risk, it also reduces the thrill of discovery that defined past eras of travel. Some travelers are now intentionally going &quot;offline&quot; to regain this lost sense of adventure. Navigating without technology requires more resilience and allows for genuine spontaneous interactions.', 'What is lost in tech-heavy travel?', 'Safety', 'Thrill of discovery', 'Money', 'Speed', 'Thrill of discovery', 'Công nghệ làm giảm cảm giác khám phá.'),
(34, 'Workation, a hybrid of work and vacation, has redefined business travel. Instead of a quick weekend trip, professionals are staying in vacation spots for months while working remotely. This trend has revitalized off-season tourism in many coastal and mountain regions. It requires reliable infrastructure, which has prompted many rural areas to upgrade their facilities. However, it raises questions about local housing markets as digital nomads drive up rent prices.', 'What is a positive impact of &quot;workation&quot;?', 'Revitalization of off-season tourism', 'More traffic', 'Less work', 'Lower rent', 'Revitalization of off-season tourism', 'Workation giúp vực dậy du lịch trái mùa.'),
(34, 'Geotourism places the geographic character of a place—its environment, heritage, aesthetics, and culture—at the center of the experience. It aims to enhance, not just sustain, the destination. By fostering pride among residents, it encourages them to protect their local treasures. It is a highly participatory form of tourism that engages the visitor as a temporary citizen. This holistic approach ensures that travel contributes positively to the destination’s long-term health and integrity.', 'What is the focus of geotourism?', 'Geographic character/heritage', 'Cheap hotels', 'Fast flights', 'Souvenirs', 'Geographic character/heritage', 'Geotourism tập trung vào đặc trưng địa phương.');

-- 35. Work &amp; Career (B2) - topic_id = 35
INSERT INTO &quot;story&quot; (&quot;topic_id&quot;, &quot;story_content&quot;, &quot;question&quot;, &quot;option_a&quot;, &quot;option_b&quot;, &quot;option_c&quot;, &quot;option_d&quot;, &quot;correct_answer&quot;, &quot;explanation_vi&quot;) VALUES 
(35, 'The &quot;gig economy&quot; has fundamentally restructured the traditional employer-employee contract. While it offers unparalleled flexibility and autonomy, it often comes at the cost of job security and benefits. Workers are now responsible for their own professional development, insurance, and retirement planning. This shift demands a high level of entrepreneurial spirit even from those who are not strictly business owners. As companies increasingly rely on contractors, the workforce must adapt to a project-based rather than role-based career trajectory.', 'What is the cost of the gig economy?', 'Flexibility', 'Job security/benefits', 'Professional growth', 'Autonomy', 'Job security/benefits', 'Kinh tế chia sẻ thiếu sự đảm bảo việc làm.'),
(35, 'Navigating corporate politics is an inevitable aspect of professional life, often overshadowing technical proficiency in determining promotion paths. Mastery of this terrain involves understanding unspoken power dynamics and building coalitions across departments. It is not necessarily about manipulation; rather, it is about aligning one’s goals with the broader strategic objectives of the organization. Those who ignore this social dimension of work often find themselves sidelined despite their hard work. Being effective requires both technical skill and political acumen.', 'Why is navigating corporate politics important?', 'To manipulate others', 'To align goals and get promoted', 'To be technical', 'To quit faster', 'To align goals and get promoted', 'Hiểu văn hóa công sở giúp thăng tiến.'),
(35, 'The concept of a &quot;portfolio career&quot; is becoming the new standard for the modern professional. Instead of staying within a single industry for decades, professionals now curate a diverse set of income streams and experiences. This diversification acts as an insurance policy against industry-specific economic downturns. It requires a mindset of constant reinvention and the ability to pivot when market demands shift. For those who thrive on variety and challenge, this approach is far more stable than the traditional single-career ladder.', 'What is a portfolio career?', 'Diverse income streams', 'Staying in one job', 'Having no work', 'Working for one boss', 'Diverse income streams', 'Sự nghiệp đa danh mục giúp giảm rủi ro.'),
(35, 'Remote work has permanently altered the geography of careers, decoupling high-paying roles from expensive urban centers. This shift allows for greater geographic freedom, yet it poses challenges for onboarding and team integration. Without casual &quot;water cooler&quot; moments, organizations must be deliberate about fostering a sense of belonging. The hybrid model is emerging as the consensus, aiming to capture the benefits of remote work without sacrificing collaborative innovation. It is an ongoing experiment in professional culture.', 'What is a challenge of remote work?', 'Cost', 'Team integration', 'Too much office time', 'Lack of technology', 'Team integration', 'Khó khăn trong việc kết nối đội ngũ khi làm từ xa.'),
(35, 'Emotional Intelligence (EQ) is increasingly being recognized as a more reliable indicator of leadership success than high IQ. The ability to manage one’s own emotions and influence others in a positive direction is essential for team morale. As work becomes more complex and collaborative, the &quot;lone genius&quot; archetype is being replaced by the empathetic facilitator. Leaders with high EQ are better equipped to handle change and navigate high-stress situations. This skill is becoming a prerequisite for advancement in all sectors.', 'Why is EQ important for leaders?', 'To be smart', 'To manage emotions/team', 'To work alone', 'To be fast', 'To manage emotions/team', 'EQ giúp quản lý cảm xúc và đội ngũ.'),
(35, 'The &quot;right to disconnect&quot; is a growing legislative trend that protects employees from the expectation of being available after hours. With the proliferation of digital communication, the boundary between work and personal life has eroded dangerously. Employers are increasingly being held accountable for the mental health impacts of &quot;always-on&quot; culture. This shift acknowledges that true productivity requires periods of total rest. It is a necessary correction to the hyper-connectivity that has plagued the modern workforce.', 'What is the &quot;right to disconnect&quot;?', 'Staying late', 'Avoiding after-hours work', 'Working fast', 'Quitting', 'Avoiding after-hours work', 'Quyền được ngắt kết nối bảo vệ cân bằng cuộc sống.'),
(35, 'AI-driven recruitment tools are changing how candidates are screened and hired. While these tools promise to reduce human bias, they often introduce new, algorithmic forms of discrimination. Applicants must learn to navigate these systems by understanding the keywords and structures the bots look for. However, there is a risk that this turns job hunting into a hollow game of optimizing for an algorithm. Human recruiters are still essential, but the initial filtering is increasingly becoming a technological black box.', 'What is a risk of AI recruitment?', 'It is slow', 'Algorithmic discrimination', 'Too cheap', 'Hard to use', 'Algorithmic discrimination', 'AI có thể tạo ra định kiến thuật toán mới.');</sql><current_tab id="0"/></tab_sql></sqlb_project>
